<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="514" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 Hunt Company, William/42:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-29T19:00:00-04:00">June 29, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>194. Your 318, June 27, 11 a.m., in regard to hoisting of American flag
                            over China Merchants’ property at Kiukiang. Your request approved. It is
                            suggested that, if you find that the Chinese Government did in fact
                            issue instructions to the Kiukiang manager to hoist the American flag
                            over China Merchants’ properties there, you ask the Chinese Foreign
                            Office to have that instruction cancelled. Please report further
                            developments.</p>
                        <p>Please repeat to Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>